= content_for(:page_title) do
  Migrating to the Icon Engine

.max-w-prose
  = doc_info(url: "https://github.com/Rails-Designer/icons", icon: "sparkles", icon_css: "text-primary") do
    :markdown
      _Loco_**Motion** now renders every icon through a small, pluggable
      **icon engine** built on the [`icons`](https://github.com/Rails-Designer/icons)
      gem — so you can use Heroicons, Lucide, Phosphor, and more from one API.

.prose
  :markdown
    # Migrating to the Icon Engine

    Earlier versions of LocoMotion depended on `rails_heroicon`, which shipped
    the entire Heroicons set inside the gem and exposed a `hero_icon` helper.
    That has been replaced by the `loco_icon` engine: LocoMotion bundles only
    a tiny set of icons and resolves everything else from the icons you **sync
    into your own app** — the same way [Tailwind](https://tailwindcss.com) only
    ships the CSS you actually use.

    This guide covers everything you need to change. Most apps only touch two
    things: run one sync command, and rename `hero_icon` to `loco_icon`.

.mt-12.prose
  :markdown
    ## 1. Sync your icons

    LocoMotion bundles just the handful of icons its own components need
    (`check`, `x-mark`, `trash`, and the calendar chevrons). Everything else —
    including most of Heroicons — now lives in your app. Sync the full
    Heroicons set once and commit the SVGs:

.max-w-prose
  = daisy_code(css: "my-4", prefix: "$") do
    bin/rails loco_motion:icons:add heroicons

.mt-4.prose
  :markdown
    Prefer to ship only what you use? Run the treeshaking sync instead — it
    scans your app (and a configurable safelist) and vendors only the icons
    you reference:

.max-w-prose
  = daisy_code(css: "my-4", prefix: "$") do
    bin/rails loco_motion:icons:sync

.mt-4.prose
  :markdown
    Either command writes SVGs into `app/assets/svg/icons/` — commit them, and
    they render as inline `<svg>` with no runtime dependency on any gem.

.mt-12.prose
  :markdown
    ## 2. Replace `hero_icon` with `loco_icon`

    The `hero_icon` helper (and the `heroicon` alias) have been removed. Rename
    calls to `loco_icon` — the arguments are the same:

.max-w-prose
  = doc_code(css: "my-4", language: "haml") do
    :plain
      -# Before
      = hero_icon("academic-cap")
      = hero_icon("bolt", variant: :solid)

      -# After
      = loco_icon("academic-cap")
      = loco_icon("bolt", variant: :solid)

.mt-12.prose
  :markdown
    ## 3. Replace `Hero::IconComponent`

    The `Hero::IconComponent` wrapper has also been removed. Anywhere you
    rendered it directly, use the `loco_icon` helper instead:

.max-w-prose
  = doc_code(css: "my-4", language: "haml") do
    :plain
      -# Before
      = render(Hero::IconComponent.new(icon: "star"))

      -# After
      = loco_icon("star")

.mt-12.prose
  :markdown
    ## 4. Component icon options

    Options like `icon:`, `left_icon:`, `right_icon:`, and the Timeline event's
    `middle_icon:` now resolve through the same engine. They work with **no
    setup for the bundled icons**, but any other name — like
    `information-circle` — must be synced first (see step 1):

.max-w-prose
  = doc_code(css: "my-4", language: "haml") do
    :plain
      = daisy_button("Save", icon: "check")          -# bundled, no sync
      = daisy_alert(icon: "information-circle")       -# needs a sync

.mt-12.prose
  :markdown
    ## 5. Libraries and variants

    You can still pass `variant:` and `library:`, but the engine also accepts a
    single **token** in the form `library:name/variant`. This is handy when the
    icon name is dynamic or when you want everything in one string:

.max-w-prose
  = doc_code(css: "my-4", language: "haml") do
    :plain
      = loco_icon("bolt", variant: :solid)      -# kwargs
      = loco_icon("bolt/solid")                 -# token: name + variant
      = loco_icon("lucide:heart")               -# token: another library
      = loco_icon("phosphor:gear/bold")         -# token: library + variant

.mt-4.prose
  :markdown
    Add more libraries the same way you added Heroicons — run
    `bin/rails loco_motion:icons:list` to see the options.

.mt-12.prose
  :markdown
    ## Summary

    - Run `loco_motion:icons:add heroicons` (or `:sync`) once and commit the SVGs.
    - Rename `hero_icon` / `heroicon` to `loco_icon`.
    - Replace `Hero::IconComponent` with `loco_icon`.
    - Sync any icon a component references that isn't in the bundled set.
